title: SM1_N1
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from exosome pellets using the miRNeasy Micro Kit (Qiagen)
extract_protocol_ch1.1: Small RNA libraries were prepared and amplified using the NEBNext small RNA Library Prep Set (New England BioLabs). Amplified libraries were resolved on a 10% polyacrylamide gel for size selection. The 140 to 160 nucleotide bands corresponding to adapter-ligated constructs derived from the 21 to 40 nucleotide RNA fragments were excised and recovered in a DNA elution buffer. The average size distribution of each library was determined using Agilent Bioanalyzer with High Sensitivity Chip Kit (Agilent) and quantified on ABI 7900HT Fast RT-PCR instrument using the KAPA Library Quantification kit (Kapa Biosystems). Each library was adjusted to final concentration of 2 nM, pooled and sequenced on an Illumina HiSeq 2000 sequencer for single-read 50 cycles.
description: Exosomal microRNAs were extracted from the serum of a healthy adult
data_processing: The BCL files were demultiplexed using CASAVA 1.8.2 (Illumina) into FASTQ files.
data_processing.1: Raw sequencing reads were then analyzed using miRDeep2 to quantify known small RNA species.
data_processing.3: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: tab-delimited csv files include read counts and normalized values for each sample.
